  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 6.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "That dwelt in the cities of Judah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". As vers. 4 and 5 referred to the dwellers in Jerusalem, so this verse tells of the dwellers in other cities, villages, etc., of the surrounding country (so ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 30:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Their ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "tithes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "of holy things",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " probably denote the \"heave offerings\" of Aaron (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 18:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; for other references to the matter of this verse, see ",
